<p>Changeip.com provides a DNS (Domain Name System) service that allows users to map a domain name to their dynamic IP address. When a user signs up for their service, they provide them with a domain name and a client software.</p>
<p>The client software is installed on the user's computer or network device which is connected to the internet. The software periodically checks the user's IP address and notifies changeip.com of any changes in the IP address.</p>
<p>When the user's IP address changes, changeip.com's DNS server is updated with the new IP address. This ensures that the user's domain name always points to their current IP address, allowing them to access their devices remotely or host a website or server without any interruption.</p>
<p>Besides, changeip.com offers additional features such as domain forwarding, email forwarding, and multiple domain support.</p></div>

